The paper proposes a constraint programming approach for task allocation and motion scheduling for industrial manipulation and assembly tasks, which involves robotics, optimization, and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions the use of heuristics and optimization techniques, which are common in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with spatiotemporal requirements and task-specific combinatorial or ordering constraints, which are relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
